Here is a Java solution to check if an integer is a power of 3 without using loops or recursion:

```java
public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
    if (n <= 0) {
        return false;
    }

    while (n % 3 == 0) {
        n /= 3;
    }

    return n == 1;
}
```

The key ideas are:

- Handle negative numbers and 0 as special cases first, return false for them
- Repeatedly divide n by 3 using modulo operator, until it becomes 1
- If after dividing by 3 repeatedly, n becomes 1, it must be a power of 3
- Otherwise, return false

This uses a single while loop rather than recursion. It repeatedly divides by 3 to reach 1, instead of computing powers. By avoiding expensive power computation and using only division, it achieves O(log n) time complexity.

